  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money (from criminal activities) appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Intentionally disguising the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transferring money to hide its illegal source\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained money seem legally earned\n\nPenalties often involve significant fines and potential criminal prosecution.",
